name: Moth
description: How many ridiculous years have rushed by to bring this spring closer. Moths, without looking, fly to the light, I fly to the sound like this. The wings are in ashes, and the Phoenix bird is reborn again from the gray days. To collect yourself in parts, to take off, to rise again from your knees, and to pray differently, and to distinguish the whisper of the stars in the vanity of losses ...
